        <section>
          <p>Satisfied customers are integral to the success of every business.
            Numerous factors combine to create a platform that customers may
            feel is convenient for them. If these factors are effectively
            applied, your customers chances of return increase significantly.
            Creating an accommodating and sustainable post-purchase platform is
            vital to building an impactful customer experience for your
            E-commerce business. If this term is new for you, let’s dive deeper
            into what it means for your E-commerce platform.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>What Does A Sustainable Post-Purchase Platform Mean?</h4>
          <p>A sustainable post-purchase platform is a business’ way of securing
            its customers longterm by catering to their post-purchase needs.
            What most brands need to realize is that their responsibility
            towards the customers continues once the customers have made the
            payment for their purchase. In reality, the significance of their
            role is amplified after this step.</p>
          <p>Creating a friendly post-purchase customer experience is crucial to
            maintaining your business’s integrity. Not only is it advantageous
            for consumers, but it also helps you cut down costs, drive
            incremental revenue, and build customer loyalty.</p>
          <figure class='blog-image-full'>
            <img
              src='/assets/images/plants-image.png'
              alt='Hand holding a plant image'
            />
            <figcaption>Image credit: pexels.com</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>What Is The Importance Of A Sustainable Post-Purchase Platform?</h4>
          <p>A sustainable post-purchase platform for your E-commerce business
            promotes goodwill between the customers and your brand. You would
            add the following benefits to the cart by focusing on sustainability
            for a post-purchase customer experience.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Increases Repeat Purchases</h4>
          <p>Once your customers are convinced of your dedication to providing
            them ease during and after purchasing, they will likely come back to
            you rather than start from scratch with another business. Repeat
            purchases promote business growth since these content customers will
            refer your business to their acquaintances. As a result, your
            business is receiving ample advertising without any extra costs from
            you.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Encourages Customer Loyalty</h4>
          <p>Customer loyalty is another gain for your E-commerce business by
            providing an excellent post-purchase platform. A market-competitive
            post-purchase customer experience strengthens customer loyalty to
            your brand. Thus, even if your competition is providing them the
            same products or services as you are at a lower price, they will
            still favor your business over them.</p>
          <figure class='blog-image-full only-mobile'>
            <img
              src='/assets/images/lights-and-sign.png'
              alt='A street sign next to a green light'
            />
            <figcaption>Image credit: unsplash.com</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Boosts Customer Retention</h4>
          <p>Your business’s ability to retain customers is directly
            proportional to the success of your business. Moreover, it helps
            your business benefit from cost reductions in gathering new
            customers. This increases profits, order value, and low promotion
            costs for your business.</p>
        </section>
        <section class='quote'>
          <div class='quote-icon'>
            <img src='assets/images/quote-icon.svg' />
          </div>
          <blockquote>Your business’s ability to retain customers is directly
            proportional to the success of your business.</blockquote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Enhances Shopping Experience</h4>
          <p>For most customers, shopping is not only about fulfilling a need or
            want. It is also a form of therapy for people. Spending on
            themselves makes consumers feel good and immediately lightens their
            mood. The whole E-commerce shopping experience highlights the
            unparalleled excitement and glee felt by the customer when receiving
            a product.</p>
          <p>A consumer-centered post-purchase platform is a critical element
            that allows such emotions to be felt by the customers. If that works
            well, consumers will repeatedly choose your brand for their shopping
            experience, increasing your revenue growth, customer retention, and
            much more.</p>
          <figure class='blog-image-full'>
            <img
              src='/assets/images/computer-integration.png'
              alt='A person typing on a computer'
            />
            <figcaption>Image credit: unsplash.com</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Tips To Create A Sustainable Post-Purchase Experience For
            Customers</h4>
          <p>Now that you have covered the whats and whys of having a
            post-purchase customer experience, it is time to explore the tips
            that will help you achieve this task while keeping sustainability in
            mind.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Provide Accurate Shipment Details</h4>
          <p>There is nothing else that customers wait so eagerly for than their
            orders to reach their doorsteps finally. Not only do they want rapid
            deliveries they also want to keep track of when they will receive
            their favorite items. Now that E-commerce has become the hub of
            purchases worldwide, consumers expect more details regarding their
            packages. An ideal way of giving customers what they want is to keep
            them involved in the shipment process so they can estimate when they
            can enjoy their purchases. Providing them with expected delivery
            dates is also a sure way of ensuring they are not missing out on a
            well-rounded shopping experience. Such a move will leave a lasting
            impression on your customers while increasing consumer engagement
            and promoting loyalty in the long run.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>Dedicated Customer Service</h4>
          <p>Dedicated customer service serves as a magnet in attracting
            customers to your business. It is also an integral aspect of your
            business that helps retain customers. Providing help to customers at
            every step of their shopping affair serves as a successful
            post-purchase customer experience. Committed customer service
            establishes growth trends for your business while enhancing your
            customer&#39;s post-purchase experience. One way to nail the
            customer service encounter is to deliver personalized responses to
            any queries your customers may face. This way, they feel prioritized
            and have a stronger connection to your business.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4>A Strong Return Policy</h4>
          <p>A firm return policy is an option most E-commerce businesses fail
            to provide their customers. Although it is a guaranteed way of
            having a winning post-purchase platform, it is still something that
            companies can’t excel at. Since consumers make their buying
            decisions by looking at a picture on the web, when that product
            finally reaches them, it may be different from what they are looking
            for. In this case, it serves no purpose to them, and they want to
            opt for a return policy. An appealing return policy makes customers
            feel secure knowing the seller will refund their money. Businesses
            that provide this guarantee have an edge compared to those that do
            not have this option.</p>
